A monitor for MELT (see http://gcc-melt.org/ for more) on Linux with a
web interface, using Boehm GC

To compile it, you need 
    sqlite3 from  http://sqlite.org
    glib-2.0 & gmodule-2.0 from GTK3 see  https://developer.gnome.org/glib/
    gmime from  https://developer.gnome.org/gmime/
    onion from https://github.com/davidmoreno/onion
    Boehm GC from http://www.hboehm.info/gc/

This code is free software (GPLv3+) in pre-alpha stage in april 2014.

To test it, first build a sqlite3 database with

   sqlite3 state-monimelt.dbsqlite < state-monimelt.sql

then run

   ./monimelt -W localhost:8086 -J 2   

and try browsing http://localhost:8086/webdir/testform.html or
http://localhost:8086/status